                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.516/151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-17T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 17, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Your 93, June 16, 4 p.m. Please cable confirmation that decree was in fact
                    promulgated yesterday, modifying Article 39 of the Organic Law of the Central
                    Bank in the form given in your telegram.</p>
                <p>Has the second decree appointing six directors by the Executive been promulgated?
                    If so, cable text and date of promulgation. Also cable text of decree modifying
                    Article 34 and date of promulgation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
